Difficult Estimation Correlation, a meta-metric for evaluation and selection of the best difficulty estimator:
Kendall's tau-b correlation of model m's difficulty (true) and prediction
Naive heuristic-based difficulty estimators fail. Trained or artificial crowd approaches work best.
We want data where models struggle to reveal headroom.
Difficulty estimators filter out easy texts (already used for WMT 2025 general machine translation shared task).
Translation testsets are easy. SotA is mostly "perfect". Clearly, MT is not perfect, but benchmarks lack behind.
What is difficulty estimation: DE("The fox jumped.") = 0% (easy to translate) DE("The mood is oddly kaleidoscopic.") = 74% (difficult)
The difficulty (defined through quality estimation) can depend on the target language or the model/translator.
By knowing what is difficult to translate, we can focus efforts towards even better translation quality.
